Node Selectors are great for basic pod placement based on node labels. But what if you need more control over where your pods land? Enter Node Affinity! 
Node Affinity lets you define complex rules for where your pods can be scheduled based on node labels.

Properties in Node Affinity

1. requiredDuringSchedulingIgnoredDuringExecution
2. preferredDuringSchedulingIgnoredDuringExecution

apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  labels:
    run: redis
  name: redis-3
spec:
  containers:
  - image: redis
    name: redis
    resources: {}
  dnsPolicy: ClusterFirst
  restartPolicy: Always
  affinity:
    nodeAffinity:
      requiredDuringSchedulingIgnoredDuringExecution:
          nodeSelectorTerms:
          - matchExpressions:
              - key: disktype
                operator: In
                values:
                - ssd
